        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Spicer Transmission Division Service Topics Number: 79</title>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Subject</title>
                <para>Transmission coming out of gear in 6/7 gear position for 7 speed transmissions.</para>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Transmission models affected:</title>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>ES52-7A</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>ES52-7B</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>ESO65-7A</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>ESO66-7B</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Symptoms:</title>
                <para>Shift lever may back out of gear slowly or may spring back out of gear.</para>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Possible causes:</title>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Synchronizers, mainshaft gears and/or shift forks may be mixed between straight and back
                            taper design.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Insufficient clutch tooth engagement.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Worn clutching teeth on 6th or 7th gear.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>What to do:</title>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Disassemble unit and check for back taper clutching teeth on mainshaft gears. Refer to
                            Transmission Parts List
                            <emph type="bold">#T210-ES52-7B</emph>
                            or International Parts Information Letter
                            <emph type="bold">PIL97-13-01</emph>. Replace worn components with the proper parts along
                            with service upgrade kit
                            <emph type="bold">49-494-6X</emph>.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Examine tooth pointing for worn or chipped teeth, if bad replace components. Check for
                            contamination on synchronizer race, if evident, replace with new parts and again include
                            service upgrade kit.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>If unit has correct components and they are not worn, chipped or contaminated use the
                            service upgrade kit
                            <emph type="bold">49-494-6X</emph>
                            that includes the following parts.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
                <table id="t0013022">
                    <title>Part Number: 49-494-6X</title>
                    <tgroup cols="3">
                        <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.05in"/>
                        <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.48in"/>
                        <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="2.47in"/>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                    <para>(1)</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                    <para>101-118-1</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">
                                    <para>Gasket-Tower</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                    <para>(1)</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2" align="center">
